    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "PadMeterZeros",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to format a given numeric input by padding it with leading zeros to ensure a consistent string length. This function is typically used in scenarios where numeric identifiers, such as meter numbers, need to be standardized to a fixed length for uniformity in reporting or data processing."
        }
